{
  "_metadata": {
    "model": "claude-fable-5",
    "cost_usd": 0.12984475,
    "duration_s": 42.985
  },
  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "name": "Glob",
      "args": {
        "pattern": "stm32-project.jsonc"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "pwd",
        "description": "Show current working directory"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Grep",
      "args": {
        "pattern": "device_family",
        "path": "stm32-project.jsonc",
        "output_mode": "content"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug start --n6-dev-mode",
        "description": "Start STM32 debug session (N6 dev mode)"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "AskUserQuestion",
      "args": {
        "questions": [
          {
            "question": "Is the NUCLEO-N6 board's BOOT switch in the DEV position?",
            "header": "BOOT switch",
            "options": [
              {
                "label": "Yes, in DEV position",
                "description": "I'll confirm the prompt and start the debug session."
              },
              {
                "label": "No / not sure",
                "description": "Flip the BOOT switch to DEV and power-cycle the board first; debug attach will fail in flash-boot position."
              }
            ],
            "multiSelect": false
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "Descriptor found in cwd \u2014 `device_family: STM32N6`, so I'll start with `--n6-dev-mode` and let the ELF autodiscover from `debug.elf_path`.\nThe session didn't start yet \u2014 the substrate requires explicit confirmation that the **BOOT switch is in the DEV position** before attaching to an STM32N6 (in flash-boot position the debug port isn't open and the attach will fail).\n\nCan you confirm the BOOT switch on the N6 board is set to DEV? Once you confirm, I'll re-run:\n\n```\necho y | stm32 debug start --n6-dev-mode\n```\n\n(answering the CLI's `n6_dev_mode: confirm BOOT switch is in DEV position` prompt affirmatively) and report the session result. If it's not in DEV, flip it and power-cycle the board first."
}